CatDescriptText: A World War II single-engine airplane in disrepair inside a workshop or hanger.  The airplane is labeled 'Firestone' in the front.  On the fuselage is painted a coat of arms: a dark colored shield with a two-handled cup surmounted by three feathers, a crest showing a hand holding a key, and a banner (with an illegible motto?) below.  Surrounding the plane are various welding and workshop tools.
TitMainTitle: Airplane hangar with single wing military airplane with "Prestone" written on nose and coat of arms showing trophy and three ostrich feathers on side
